22 July 2015The Minister of Communications, Faith Muthambi, will visit China from the 23rd to the 27th of July 2015 to interact with her Chinese counterparts on various issues relating to communications.During the five-day visit to Beijing, Muthambi will meet the Minister of State Administration of Press, Publication Radio Film and Television, as well as the Minister of State Council Information Office.Minister Muthambi will use the trip to gain more insights on the role that information and knowledge sharing can play in fostering economic growth while also fastracking socio-economic development and transformation. This visit serves as good opportunity to learn more about China and its development in broadcast and the broader TV industry. It is also meant to lay a foundation for further exchange and cooperation in these fields between the two countries, she said.Minister will be accompanied by senior executives from SABC, and Broadcasting Digital Migration team from the Ministry of Communications. For enquiries: Mish Molakeng Cell:082 469 3997 Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) on behalf of the Ministry of Communications